ATTACK
  Launch a ground assault on an enemy sector.

SYNTAX
  attack <target-x,y> <attacking-sects> [land-units]
  atta   <target-x,y> <attacking-sects> [land-units]

DESCRIPTION
  Attacks an adjacent enemy sector with military from one or more
  of your neighboring sectors.  The result depends on relative
  military strength, efficiency, and tech levels.

  If the attack succeeds, you capture the sector.  It will have 0%
  efficiency under your control initially.  The previous owner's
  civilians and resources remain in the sector.

  Attack strength scales with:
    - number of attacking military
    - efficiency of attacking sectors
    - tech level of your nation
    - land units committed (if any)

  Defense strength scales with:
    - defending military
    - sector efficiency and fortress bonus
    - defender's tech level

  Attacking costs military lives on both sides regardless of outcome.

EXAMPLE
  attack 2,0 0,0            attack 2,0 from your capital
  attack -2,2 -3,1 -1,1    attack from two adjacent sectors

SEE ALSO
  march  bomb  relations  declare  census
